        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46507",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jgornick",
                        "name": "jgornick",
                        "displayName": "Joe Gornick",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The issue here is that CONTENT_TYPE and CONTENT_LENGTH are not prefixed with HTTP_.  The reason is because CONTENT_TYPE and CONTENT_LENGTH are not protocol specific meta-variables (http:\/\/www.ietf.org\/rfc\/rfc3875).\r\n\r\nSo, unless you have the apache_request_headers method available, the type and length of the request are never obtained for the request.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jgornick",
                        "name": "jgornick",
                        "displayName": "Joe Gornick",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-05-09T19:39:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-05-09T19:39:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46508",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ashawley",
                        "name": "ashawley",
                        "displayName": "Aaron S. Hawley",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Never say, \"never\".\r\n\r\nThe current test in Zend_Controller_Request_HttpTest::testGetHeader() has\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n$_SERVER['HTTP_CONTENT_TYPE']    = 'text\/json';\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nSo it would seem some PHP environments do put HTTP_CONTENT_TYPE in $_SERVER.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure what the appropriate patch to Zend_Controller_Request_Http is, but I know I add this to dispatch script (public\/index.php).\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nif (isset($_SERVER['CONTENT_TYPE'])\r\n    && !isset($_SERVER['HTTP_CONTENT_TYPE'])\r\n) {\r\n    $_SERVER['HTTP_CONTENT_TYPE'] = $_SERVER['CONTENT_TYPE'];\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ashawley",
                        "name": "ashawley",
                        "displayName": "Aaron S. Hawley",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-05-09T19:51:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-05-09T19:51:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46509",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jgornick",
                        "name": "jgornick",
                        "displayName": "Joe Gornick",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'd be interested to find out what environments return HTTP_CONTENT_TYPE.\r\n\r\nIn regards to a patch for HTTP requests, I would say we try to load the requested meta variable without the HTTP prefix, then if not found, add the HTTP prefix and try that.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jgornick",
                        "name": "jgornick",
                        "displayName": "Joe Gornick",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-05-09T20:31:17.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-05-09T20:31:17.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46516",
                    "author": {
